ecause leases are designed for longer commitments, and 41 months falls cleanly within a 48-month term with a simple early exit. Specific Deal Available NOW (April 2026): 2026 Hyundai Elantra SE Monthly: $199/month (36-month lease in NY) Down: $3,999 due at signing Mileage: 10,000 miles/year (standard) Can negotiate 48-month term at approx. $225–$240/month 2026 Honda Civic LX Monthly: $209/month (36-month lease in NY) Down: $3,899 due at signing Mileage: 10,000 miles/year 48-month pricing: $240–$260/month estimated COST BREAKDOWN: 41-MONTH HYUNDAI ELANTRA LEASE Scenario: 48-month lease at $225/month, exit at month 41 Cost Component\tAmount\tNotes Monthly payment × 41 months\t$9,225\t($225 × 41) Down payment at signing\t$3,999\tCapitalized cost reduction Registration/Tags (NY)\t$150–$250\tOne-time at lease start Early termination fee (month 41)\t$800–$1,200\tTypical lease buyout; negotiate waiver with dealer Remaining mileage buffer\t$0\t41mo × 833mi/mo = 34,153 miles (within 40,000 limit) ✓ TOTAL 41-MONTH COST\t$14,174–$14,674 Monthly equivalent cost\t$346/month\tIncludes all-in costs vs. Your Previous 12-month Option at $1,250/month = $15,000 total You save: $826–$1,326 over 41 months OR $19–$32/month CRITICAL MILEAGE ANALYSIS (Your Daily Harlem→White Plains Commute) This is where leases either WIN or KILL you. Your annual mileage: 25 miles each way × 5 days/week × 52 weeks = 13,000 miles/year Standard lease allowance: 10,000 miles/year YOU EXCEED BY 3,000 miles/year Over 41 months (3.42 years): Actual miles needed: 44,460 miles Standard lease allowance: 34,167 miles (10K × 3.42 years) OVERAGE: 10,293 miles × $0.25/mile = $2,573 excess mileage penalty CRITICAL DECISION POINT: Option A1: Negotiate \"Mileage Overage\" at lease signing Prepay excess mileage at $0.18/mile instead of $0.25/mile at return Cost: 10,293 miles × $0.18 = $1,853 (saves $720 vs. pay-at-end) Add to down payment, making effective cost = $5,852 due at signing Option A2: Reduce commute or split dri